[WAVES]

00:00:15.936 --> 00:00:22.410 align:middle line:90%


00:00:22.410 --> 00:00:26.394 align:middle line:90%
[HEART BEATING]

00:00:26.394 --> 00:00:29.880 align:middle line:90%


00:00:29.880 --> 00:00:33.864 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC - PINK FLOYD, "TIME"]

00:00:33.864 --> 00:00:43.840 align:middle line:90%


00:00:43.840 --> 00:00:45.082 align:middle line:90%
>> Trees.

00:00:45.082 --> 00:00:48.040 align:middle line:90%


00:00:48.040 --> 00:00:51.510 align:middle line:84%
Trees are the lifeblood
of our worlds.

00:00:51.510 --> 00:00:53.970 align:middle line:84%
Without them, there would
be no life on Earth.

00:00:53.970 --> 00:00:57.810 align:middle line:90%
[SIRENS]

00:00:57.810 --> 00:00:59.250 align:middle line:90%


00:00:59.250 --> 00:01:01.620 align:middle line:84%
Since the beginning of
time, we have been at war

00:01:01.620 --> 00:01:05.942 align:middle line:84%
with ourselves and
our environment.

00:01:05.942 --> 00:01:10.802 align:middle line:90%


00:01:10.802 --> 00:01:13.250 align:middle line:90%
Violence infects our worlds.

00:01:13.250 --> 00:01:17.520 align:middle line:10%
It lives in our streets,
our communities,

00:01:17.520 --> 00:01:19.535 align:middle line:10%
and now, even in our schools.

00:01:19.535 --> 00:01:22.340 align:middle line:90%


00:01:22.340 --> 00:01:26.390 align:middle line:84%
Environmental destruction
ravages our planet.

00:01:26.390 --> 00:01:30.080 align:middle line:10%
As we continue to destroy
the great fabric of life,

00:01:30.080 --> 00:01:33.610 align:middle line:10%
our world is turned upside
down, and in turn, our world

00:01:33.610 --> 00:01:36.680 align:middle line:10%
is sick, very sick.

00:01:36.680 --> 00:01:38.960 align:middle line:84%
I was committed
to finding peace.

00:01:38.960 --> 00:01:41.225 align:middle line:84%
For me, my journey
began with trees.

00:01:41.225 --> 00:01:44.390 align:middle line:90%


00:01:44.390 --> 00:01:46.100 align:middle line:90%
My name is Greg Reitman.

00:01:46.100 --> 00:01:49.064 align:middle line:90%
This is my story.

00:01:49.064 --> 00:01:51.504 align:middle line:84%
(SINGING) Ticking
away the moments

00:01:51.504 --> 00:01:53.456 align:middle line:90%
that make up a dull day.

00:01:53.456 --> 00:01:56.384 align:middle line:90%


00:01:56.384 --> 00:02:02.260 align:middle line:84%
Fritter and waste the
hours in an offhand way.

00:02:02.260 --> 00:02:05.530 align:middle line:10%
>> I didn't know how to
think as a human being.

00:02:05.530 --> 00:02:08.520 align:middle line:10%
I wouldn't know how to
think as a human being.

00:02:08.520 --> 00:02:12.480 align:middle line:10%
I wouldn't know how to
walk as a human being.

00:02:12.480 --> 00:02:18.598 align:middle line:84%
I learn all of these
from other human beings.

00:02:18.598 --> 00:02:22.590 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:22.590 --> 00:02:26.582 align:middle line:90%


00:02:26.582 --> 00:02:28.580 align:middle line:90%
Where is your grace?

00:02:28.580 --> 00:02:31.410 align:middle line:90%
Why fight?

00:02:31.410 --> 00:02:32.360 align:middle line:90%
>> You have war.

00:02:32.360 --> 00:02:33.360 align:middle line:90%
[GUNSHOTS]

00:02:33.360 --> 00:02:34.860 align:middle line:90%
[EXPLOSION]

00:02:34.860 --> 00:02:38.990 align:middle line:10%
And you have destruction
of the ecosystem.

00:02:38.990 --> 00:02:41.570 align:middle line:10%
>> What I think escapes our
attention is that just about

00:02:41.570 --> 00:02:44.090 align:middle line:10%
everything we do is violent.

00:02:44.090 --> 00:02:46.720 align:middle line:90%
Our agriculture is violent.

00:02:46.720 --> 00:02:48.580 align:middle line:84%
What happens to creatures
and the critters

00:02:48.580 --> 00:02:51.550 align:middle line:84%
in the soil happens to the
soil itself is violent.

00:02:51.550 --> 00:02:54.620 align:middle line:90%


00:02:54.620 --> 00:02:59.950 align:middle line:84%
>> It's so obvious that we're
inextricably intertwined with

00:02:59.950 --> 00:03:02.910 align:middle line:90%
all of nature.

00:03:02.910 --> 00:03:05.070 align:middle line:84%
>> I heard this
word enlightenment,

00:03:05.070 --> 00:03:08.160 align:middle line:84%
and I wondered if
it is possible.

00:03:08.160 --> 00:03:11.200 align:middle line:84%
Does a human being
have this potential?

00:03:11.200 --> 00:03:13.504 align:middle line:90%
>> Why are we so crazy?

00:03:13.504 --> 00:03:14.540 align:middle line:90%
Why are we so crazy?

00:03:14.540 --> 00:03:16.500 align:middle line:90%
[SIRENS]

00:03:16.500 --> 00:03:17.520 align:middle line:90%
>> Why are we so crazy?

00:03:17.520 --> 00:03:20.240 align:middle line:90%


00:03:20.240 --> 00:03:24.110 align:middle line:84%
Going back to my roots I thought
could provide some insight.

00:03:24.110 --> 00:03:27.140 align:middle line:84%
As a kid, I was a
major comic collector.

00:03:27.140 --> 00:03:30.830 align:middle line:84%
My first impressions of violence
came from comic book heroes

00:03:30.830 --> 00:03:32.240 align:middle line:90%
and villains.

00:03:32.240 --> 00:03:37.280 align:middle line:84%
This is my favorite
one, Clark Kent.

00:03:37.280 --> 00:03:39.350 align:middle line:90%
Pretty cool.

00:03:39.350 --> 00:03:40.220 align:middle line:90%
Oh, here's Batman.

00:03:40.220 --> 00:03:41.197 align:middle line:90%
Look at this.

00:03:41.197 --> 00:03:45.267 align:middle line:84%
[MUSIC - NEAL HEFTI, "BATMAN
 THEME"]

00:03:45.267 --> 00:03:46.067 align:middle line:90%


00:03:46.067 --> 00:03:47.041 align:middle line:90%
(SINGING) Batman.

00:03:47.041 --> 00:03:54.370 align:middle line:90%


00:03:54.370 --> 00:03:57.310 align:middle line:84%
>> Superman and Batman
were always my favorites.

00:03:57.310 --> 00:04:00.430 align:middle line:84%
But now, I can't help
but notice how violent

00:04:00.430 --> 00:04:03.010 align:middle line:90%
all these images are.

00:04:03.010 --> 00:04:04.120 align:middle line:90%
Blood and darkness.

00:04:04.120 --> 00:04:07.570 align:middle line:90%


00:04:07.570 --> 00:04:09.890 align:middle line:90%
Pretty gnarly.

00:04:09.890 --> 00:04:15.040 align:middle line:10%
>> One problem is the hero
archetype and lending a kind

00:04:15.040 --> 00:04:19.857 align:middle line:10%
of unbalanced image to us
to be very invulnerable,

00:04:19.857 --> 00:04:21.399 align:middle line:10%
rather than vulnerable
and sensitive,

00:04:21.399 --> 00:04:25.150 align:middle line:10%
to be very powerful and
to be strong and forceful,

00:04:25.150 --> 00:04:30.670 align:middle line:10%
and not yielding or
empathic and compassionate.

00:04:30.670 --> 00:04:35.650 align:middle line:10%
>> All of our celebrations are
about war or truces or battles

00:04:35.650 --> 00:04:36.610 align:middle line:10%
won.

00:04:36.610 --> 00:04:39.520 align:middle line:84%
And it always is a division
because someone loses

00:04:39.520 --> 00:04:41.920 align:middle line:90%
and someone wins.

00:04:41.920 --> 00:04:45.250 align:middle line:90%
>> So it is good versus evil.

00:04:45.250 --> 00:04:49.300 align:middle line:90%
Is it fantasy, or is it reality?

00:04:49.300 --> 00:04:53.210 align:middle line:84%
I love comics just as
much as everyone else.

00:04:53.210 --> 00:04:55.560 align:middle line:84%
But I wonder, does
their pop culture

00:04:55.560 --> 00:04:57.810 align:middle line:90%
influence our violent behavior?

00:04:57.810 --> 00:05:01.140 align:middle line:10%
>> The World Health Organization
has said that violence is

00:05:01.140 --> 00:05:02.940 align:middle line:10%
a preventable disease.

00:05:02.940 --> 00:05:04.280 align:middle line:10%
And it is.

00:05:04.280 --> 00:05:05.640 align:middle line:90%
We're not born violent.

00:05:05.640 --> 00:05:10.100 align:middle line:84%
Our culture teaches
us how to be violent.

00:05:10.100 --> 00:05:12.260 align:middle line:90%
>> Here we are at the E3 show.

00:05:12.260 --> 00:05:15.450 align:middle line:90%
We got cars, games.

00:05:15.450 --> 00:05:16.770 align:middle line:90%
And I'm on a mission.

00:05:16.770 --> 00:05:19.547 align:middle line:84%
I'm trying to find out,
is there a peace game?

00:05:19.547 --> 00:05:24.417 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC, THE KILLERS, "HUMAN"]

00:05:24.417 --> 00:05:27.826 align:middle line:84%
(SINGING) I did
my best to notice

00:05:27.826 --> 00:05:31.050 align:middle line:84%
when the call came
down the line up

00:05:31.050 --> 00:05:35.050 align:middle line:90%
to the platform of surrender.

00:05:35.050 --> 00:05:38.296 align:middle line:90%
I was broad, but I was kind.

00:05:38.296 --> 00:05:39.590 align:middle line:90%
>> Can I get one of these?

00:05:39.590 --> 00:05:40.740 align:middle line:90%
>> You certainly can.

00:05:40.740 --> 00:05:41.540 align:middle line:90%
>> What do--

00:05:41.540 --> 00:05:42.210 align:middle line:90%
>> This is a new one.

00:05:42.210 --> 00:05:44.270 align:middle line:84%
This is the 1942 game,
now available on iPhone,

00:05:44.270 --> 00:05:45.090 align:middle line:90%
iPad, yeah.

00:05:45.090 --> 00:05:46.905 align:middle line:84%
>> And what do you
think of the game?

00:05:46.905 --> 00:05:48.550 align:middle line:84%
>> Oh, it's a fun game
because you shoot things.

00:05:48.550 --> 00:05:49.420 align:middle line:90%
I always like to shoot things.

00:05:49.420 --> 00:05:50.385 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, you shoot things?

00:05:50.385 --> 00:05:51.185 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:05:51.185 --> 00:05:55.050 align:middle line:84%
I'm not saying I'm pro-war
but I like to shoot things.

00:05:55.050 --> 00:05:57.990 align:middle line:90%
>> Look at this, "God of War."

00:05:57.990 --> 00:05:59.460 align:middle line:90%
(SINGING) Cut the cord.

00:05:59.460 --> 00:06:02.890 align:middle line:90%
Are we human?

00:06:02.890 --> 00:06:04.850 align:middle line:90%
Or are we dancers?

00:06:04.850 --> 00:06:06.320 align:middle line:90%
[GUNSHOT]

00:06:06.320 --> 00:06:10.240 align:middle line:90%
My sign is vital.

00:06:10.240 --> 00:06:13.290 align:middle line:90%
My hands are cold.

00:06:13.290 --> 00:06:15.790 align:middle line:84%
>> All the signs are pointing
to the fact that we are indeed

00:06:15.790 --> 00:06:17.290 align:middle line:90%
a violent society.

00:06:17.290 --> 00:06:18.772 align:middle line:90%
But why?

00:06:18.772 --> 00:06:22.210 align:middle line:84%
>> Some of the kids know
more about weapons than I do.

00:06:22.210 --> 00:06:28.130 align:middle line:84%
>> Could you ever imagine seeing
like a peace, you know, game.

00:06:28.130 --> 00:06:32.770 align:middle line:84%
I looked throughout the halls
of the E3 show, and believe me,

00:06:32.770 --> 00:06:34.984 align:middle line:90%
there was no peace game.

00:06:34.984 --> 00:06:38.880 align:middle line:90%
[RADIO STATIC]

00:06:38.880 --> 00:06:43.263 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:06:43.263 --> 00:06:45.450 align:middle line:90%
Mm, Delicious.

00:06:45.450 --> 00:06:47.920 align:middle line:84%
Good old bacon,
sausage, and eggs.

00:06:47.920 --> 00:06:50.002 align:middle line:90%
Breakfast of champions.

00:06:50.002 --> 00:06:51.970 align:middle line:90%
[RADIO STATIC]

00:06:51.970 --> 00:06:54.940 align:middle line:84%
>> And this is causing potential
for civilian harm just can't be

00:06:54.940 --> 00:06:56.680 align:middle line:90%
justified.

00:06:56.680 --> 00:06:59.800 align:middle line:84%
>> This or any other military
operation alone will not

00:06:59.800 --> 00:07:01.768 align:middle line:90%
eliminate the threat.

00:07:01.768 --> 00:07:05.156 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:07:05.156 --> 00:07:15.070 align:middle line:90%


00:07:15.070 --> 00:07:15.870 align:middle line:90%
>> It's business.

00:07:15.870 --> 00:07:21.340 align:middle line:90%


00:07:21.340 --> 00:07:23.330 align:middle line:90%
>> [INAUDIBLE] talk to me.

00:07:23.330 --> 00:07:24.680 align:middle line:90%
>> [INAUDIBLE].

00:07:24.680 --> 00:07:27.270 align:middle line:84%
You got a huge
force that's moving.

00:07:27.270 --> 00:07:28.890 align:middle line:10%
>> There's a market for this.

00:07:28.890 --> 00:07:30.540 align:middle line:90%
Can you sell more of these?

00:07:30.540 --> 00:07:33.430 align:middle line:84%
Well, you can if
there's conflict.

00:07:33.430 --> 00:07:36.240 align:middle line:90%
>> [INAUDIBLE].

00:07:36.240 --> 00:07:40.470 align:middle line:10%
>> If we don't tell the stories
of what war does and how long

00:07:40.470 --> 00:07:46.990 align:middle line:10%
it's been doing it, if we don't
talk about what that feels

00:07:46.990 --> 00:07:52.655 align:middle line:10%
like, then we carry it forward.

00:07:52.655 --> 00:07:55.030 align:middle line:84%
>> I never talked about my
experience living in the first

00:07:55.030 --> 00:07:55.830 align:middle line:90%
Gulf War.

00:07:55.830 --> 00:08:00.880 align:middle line:90%


00:08:00.880 --> 00:08:05.200 align:middle line:84%
>> Early on January 18th, 1991,
the skies of Israel were lit up

00:08:05.200 --> 00:08:07.510 align:middle line:84%
by Scud missiles
fired from Iraq,

00:08:07.510 --> 00:08:10.780 align:middle line:84%
retaliation for the American
led offensive to oust Saddam

00:08:10.780 --> 00:08:14.390 align:middle line:90%
Hussein from Kuwait.

00:08:14.390 --> 00:08:16.850 align:middle line:90%
[SIRENS SOUNDING]

00:08:16.850 --> 00:08:17.840 align:middle line:90%


00:08:17.840 --> 00:08:20.690 align:middle line:84%
>> Within seconds I was
running into a bomb shelter.

00:08:20.690 --> 00:08:27.870 align:middle line:90%


00:08:27.870 --> 00:08:30.240 align:middle line:84%
I looked over and saw a
mother putting a gas mask

00:08:30.240 --> 00:08:32.880 align:middle line:90%
on her child's face.

00:08:32.880 --> 00:08:35.820 align:middle line:84%
I asked myself, how does
a mother explain this?

00:08:35.820 --> 00:08:42.460 align:middle line:90%


00:08:42.460 --> 00:08:44.900 align:middle line:84%
The next day, my mom
called me in tears,

00:08:44.900 --> 00:08:46.580 align:middle line:90%
wanting me to come home.

00:08:46.580 --> 00:08:49.190 align:middle line:90%
The Gulf War lasted three weeks.

00:08:49.190 --> 00:08:52.620 align:middle line:84%
But for me, that one
experience changed my life.

00:08:52.620 --> 00:08:56.985 align:middle line:90%


00:08:56.985 --> 00:08:57.955 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:08:57.955 --> 00:09:01.840 align:middle line:84%
(SINGING) Where do
we go from here?

00:09:01.840 --> 00:09:04.870 align:middle line:90%
How do we carry on?

00:09:04.870 --> 00:09:07.144 align:middle line:84%
I can't get beyond
the questions.

00:09:07.144 --> 00:09:11.530 align:middle line:90%


00:09:11.530 --> 00:09:16.420 align:middle line:84%
Clambering for the scraps
in the shatter of us

00:09:16.420 --> 00:09:20.190 align:middle line:84%
collapsed that cuts me
with every could-have-been.

00:09:20.190 --> 00:09:23.220 align:middle line:90%
>> Good old bonsai.

00:09:23.220 --> 00:09:26.080 align:middle line:10%
I didn't even know
it changed my life.

00:09:26.080 --> 00:09:27.840 align:middle line:84%
I was a student back
at UMass Amherst.

00:09:27.840 --> 00:09:30.800 align:middle line:90%


00:09:30.800 --> 00:09:33.140 align:middle line:90%
One morning, I woke in tears.

00:09:33.140 --> 00:09:35.250 align:middle line:84%
I didn't understand
why I was crying

00:09:35.250 --> 00:09:36.560 align:middle line:90%
or what was happening to me.

00:09:36.560 --> 00:09:39.370 align:middle line:90%


00:09:39.370 --> 00:09:41.100 align:middle line:90%
I had this crazy idea though.

00:09:41.100 --> 00:09:43.230 align:middle line:84%
I was going to save the
world by planting trees.

00:09:43.230 --> 00:09:46.030 align:middle line:90%
(SINGING) Time heals everything.

00:09:46.030 --> 00:09:49.140 align:middle line:84%
>> I rushed down to the Amherst
library and found the classic

00:09:49.140 --> 00:09:52.420 align:middle line:84%
Robert Frost poem
"The Sound of Trees."

00:09:52.420 --> 00:09:54.056 align:middle line:90%
It spoke to me.

00:09:54.056 --> 00:09:57.250 align:middle line:10%
I produced a fundraiser
leaflet on recycled paper

00:09:57.250 --> 00:10:00.910 align:middle line:10%
and named it The Giving
Tree, Rooted in Peace.

00:10:00.910 --> 00:10:02.335 align:middle line:10%
I was on a mission
to plant trees.

00:10:02.335 --> 00:10:06.877 align:middle line:90%


00:10:06.877 --> 00:10:07.830 align:middle line:90%
>> Have a nice day.

00:10:07.830 --> 00:10:10.220 align:middle line:90%
>> All right, you too.

00:10:10.220 --> 00:10:12.300 align:middle line:90%
Why did I shed those tears?

00:10:12.300 --> 00:10:13.850 align:middle line:90%
Why trees?

00:10:13.850 --> 00:10:17.870 align:middle line:84%
For me, these emotions took
root when I visited Hiroshima.

00:10:17.870 --> 00:10:21.390 align:middle line:90%


00:10:21.390 --> 00:10:25.900 align:middle line:10%
>> I visited, like
you, Hiroshima.

00:10:25.900 --> 00:10:31.640 align:middle line:90%
It was 1955.

00:10:31.640 --> 00:10:33.420 align:middle line:90%
>> Remember what to do, friends.

00:10:33.420 --> 00:10:35.200 align:middle line:84%
Now, tell me right
out loud, what

00:10:35.200 --> 00:10:37.727 align:middle line:84%
are you supposed to do
when you see the flash?

00:10:37.727 --> 00:10:39.158 align:middle line:90%
>> Duck!

00:10:39.158 --> 00:10:41.550 align:middle line:90%
And cover!

00:10:41.550 --> 00:10:44.400 align:middle line:90%
>> How did Hiroshima disappear?

00:10:44.400 --> 00:10:46.540 align:middle line:90%
Why did it disappear?

00:10:46.540 --> 00:10:50.020 align:middle line:84%
I'm trying to understand
why humans did this.

00:10:50.020 --> 00:10:53.290 align:middle line:84%
And the other question is,
why was Einstein afraid?

00:10:53.290 --> 00:10:57.070 align:middle line:10%
>> The only thing
we have to fear is--

00:10:57.070 --> 00:11:00.210 align:middle line:10%
>> Increasing the
risk of World War III.

00:11:00.210 --> 00:11:05.370 align:middle line:10%
>> In a language that,
in a sense, is new.

00:11:05.370 --> 00:11:09.950 align:middle line:84%
That new language is the
language of atomic warfare.

00:11:09.950 --> 00:11:16.300 align:middle line:10%
>> For a nuclear disaster,
spread by wind and water

00:11:16.300 --> 00:11:18.560 align:middle line:10%
and fear.

00:11:18.560 --> 00:11:20.730 align:middle line:10%
>> The peril of nuclear war--

00:11:20.730 --> 00:11:23.990 align:middle line:10%
>> Will be used
to defend freedom.

00:11:23.990 --> 00:11:28.520 align:middle line:10%
>> And in the nuclear era,
there is no rational alternative

00:11:28.520 --> 00:11:31.610 align:middle line:10%
to accords of mutual restraint.

00:11:31.610 --> 00:11:35.540 align:middle line:10%
>> The danger is
becoming greater.

00:11:35.540 --> 00:11:39.680 align:middle line:10%
>> Our security is based on
being prepared to meet all

00:11:39.680 --> 00:11:41.690 align:middle line:10%
threats.

00:11:41.690 --> 00:11:45.080 align:middle line:10%
>> No category of nuclear
weapons has received more

00:11:45.080 --> 00:11:48.440 align:middle line:10%
attention than those in
our strategic arsenals.

00:11:48.440 --> 00:11:52.220 align:middle line:10%
>> We're taking the next crucial
step to lift the dark cloud

00:11:52.220 --> 00:11:55.250 align:middle line:10%
of nuclear fear that is hung
over the world for 50 years

00:11:55.250 --> 00:11:56.240 align:middle line:10%
now.

00:11:56.240 --> 00:11:58.850 align:middle line:10%
>> Should make people nervous
when non-transparent regimes

00:11:58.850 --> 00:12:04.580 align:middle line:10%
that announce that they've got
nuclear warheads fire missiles.

00:12:04.580 --> 00:12:08.510 align:middle line:10%
>> If we fail to act, we will
invite nuclear arms races

00:12:08.510 --> 00:12:12.680 align:middle line:10%
in every region and the prospect
of war on a scale that we can

00:12:12.680 --> 00:12:13.720 align:middle line:10%
hardly imagine.

00:12:13.720 --> 00:12:16.940 align:middle line:10%
>> Shockwaves from the
underground nuclear test were

00:12:16.940 --> 00:12:18.530 align:middle line:10%
felt far and wide.

00:12:18.530 --> 00:12:21.290 align:middle line:10%
>> The move further heightens
tensions on the Korean

00:12:21.290 --> 00:12:22.280 align:middle line:10%
peninsula.

00:12:22.280 --> 00:12:25.565 align:middle line:84%
>> Tensions between the Islamic
republic of Iran and the West

00:12:25.565 --> 00:12:29.470 align:middle line:90%
have reached a crescendo.

00:12:29.470 --> 00:12:32.320 align:middle line:84%
>> Pakistan has tested its
latest short range missile

00:12:32.320 --> 00:12:34.510 align:middle line:84%
capable of carrying
nuclear warheads.

00:12:34.510 --> 00:12:38.170 align:middle line:84%
>> Their major focus is on
their mutual neighbor India.

00:12:38.170 --> 00:12:42.730 align:middle line:84%
>> People are stunned to realize
we spend $54 billion a year

00:12:42.730 --> 00:12:43.810 align:middle line:90%
on nuclear weapons.

00:12:43.810 --> 00:12:48.340 align:middle line:84%
That we're planning on
spending $7.3 billion--

00:12:48.340 --> 00:12:53.180 align:middle line:84%
I'm sorry, that we're planning
on spending $7.3 trillion

00:12:53.180 --> 00:12:54.970 align:middle line:90%
over the next 10 years.

00:12:54.970 --> 00:12:57.460 align:middle line:90%
$7.3 trillion?

00:12:57.460 --> 00:12:58.840 align:middle line:90%
For what?

00:12:58.840 --> 00:13:02.730 align:middle line:90%
To protect who against what?

00:13:02.730 --> 00:13:04.870 align:middle line:90%
You know, it's out of whack.

00:13:04.870 --> 00:13:05.930 align:middle line:90%
It's out of control.

00:13:05.930 --> 00:13:22.510 align:middle line:90%


00:13:22.510 --> 00:13:25.450 align:middle line:84%
>> Crazy the world we live in
and how close we are a nuclear

00:13:25.450 --> 00:13:27.040 align:middle line:90%
meltdown.

00:13:27.040 --> 00:13:29.260 align:middle line:84%
Reflecting at the United
Nations Peace Bell

00:13:29.260 --> 00:13:30.595 align:middle line:90%
took me back 20 years.

00:13:30.595 --> 00:13:33.930 align:middle line:90%


00:13:33.930 --> 00:13:35.920 align:middle line:10%
I was an overseas
student studying abroad

00:13:35.920 --> 00:13:40.420 align:middle line:10%
in Sapporo, Japan at
Hokkaido University.

00:13:40.420 --> 00:13:43.265 align:middle line:10%
One day, my friends and I decide
to visit the Hiroshima Peace

00:13:43.265 --> 00:13:44.065 align:middle line:10%
Memorial.

00:13:44.065 --> 00:13:50.610 align:middle line:90%


00:13:50.610 --> 00:13:53.975 align:middle line:84%
Tears ran down my friends' faces
as we gazed over the horrific

00:13:53.975 --> 00:13:54.775 align:middle line:90%
images.

00:13:54.775 --> 00:14:00.700 align:middle line:90%


00:14:00.700 --> 00:14:04.770 align:middle line:90%
But for me, there were no tears.

00:14:04.770 --> 00:14:07.017 align:middle line:90%
And I wondered, why?

00:14:07.017 --> 00:14:10.000 align:middle line:90%


00:14:10.000 --> 00:14:10.990 align:middle line:90%
Why didn't I cry?

00:14:10.990 --> 00:14:14.250 align:middle line:90%


00:14:14.250 --> 00:14:15.125 align:middle line:90%
Why didn't I connect?

00:14:15.125 --> 00:14:17.870 align:middle line:90%


00:14:17.870 --> 00:14:22.100 align:middle line:10%
>> The first stage usually is
one of a depersonalization,

00:14:22.100 --> 00:14:27.260 align:middle line:10%
a shock that happens so that you
feel like this can't really be

00:14:27.260 --> 00:14:29.360 align:middle line:10%
happening.

00:14:29.360 --> 00:14:32.480 align:middle line:84%
They have really cut
off their emotions.

00:14:32.480 --> 00:14:38.720 align:middle line:84%
A lot of emotion can emerge and
a lot of the physical symptoms.

00:14:38.720 --> 00:14:40.730 align:middle line:90%
You can get anger.

00:14:40.730 --> 00:14:44.270 align:middle line:84%
And the flip side of
that is depression.

00:14:44.270 --> 00:14:48.770 align:middle line:10%
Over time, the final stages
have to do with what we call,

00:14:48.770 --> 00:14:53.310 align:middle line:10%
basically, resolution
and acceptance.

00:14:53.310 --> 00:14:55.220 align:middle line:90%
>> It was all a blur.

00:14:55.220 --> 00:14:57.630 align:middle line:84%
I mean, could one traumatic
experience spill over

00:14:57.630 --> 00:14:59.030 align:middle line:90%
in one's outer life?

00:14:59.030 --> 00:15:01.020 align:middle line:10%
>> Trauma is a common reality.

00:15:01.020 --> 00:15:02.240 align:middle line:10%
It's a daily reality.

00:15:02.240 --> 00:15:03.650 align:middle line:10%
It happens everyday.

00:15:03.650 --> 00:15:05.300 align:middle line:84%
It's very unlikely
that somebody is

00:15:05.300 --> 00:15:08.840 align:middle line:84%
going to live a lifetime without
encountering traumatic events

00:15:08.840 --> 00:15:09.950 align:middle line:90%
in their lives.

00:15:09.950 --> 00:15:12.740 align:middle line:84%
The trauma vortex
is a metaphor that

00:15:12.740 --> 00:15:17.000 align:middle line:84%
is very expressive of the
dynamic nature of trauma.

00:15:17.000 --> 00:15:21.260 align:middle line:84%
Unhealed trauma, you don't just
get a symptom and you're done.

00:15:21.260 --> 00:15:22.730 align:middle line:90%
It keeps augmenting.

00:15:22.730 --> 00:15:24.620 align:middle line:90%
It keeps amplifying.

00:15:24.620 --> 00:15:29.120 align:middle line:84%
And so from something that just
made a little part of your life

00:15:29.120 --> 00:15:31.340 align:middle line:84%
dysfunctional, it
just can spread

00:15:31.340 --> 00:15:34.730 align:middle line:84%
to a bigger and bigger part
of your life and, of course,

00:15:34.730 --> 00:15:36.650 align:middle line:84%
of the life of the
people around you

00:15:36.650 --> 00:15:39.120 align:middle line:84%
and the community that you're
in, et cetera, et cetera.

00:15:39.120 --> 00:15:43.030 align:middle line:90%


00:15:43.030 --> 00:15:45.610 align:middle line:84%
>> Isn't in trauma something
we've all experienced on one

00:15:45.610 --> 00:15:48.450 align:middle line:90%
level or another?

00:15:48.450 --> 00:15:50.730 align:middle line:84%
Who could forget
9/11 and the trauma

00:15:50.730 --> 00:15:53.920 align:middle line:90%
we all experience as a country.

00:15:53.920 --> 00:15:56.480 align:middle line:84%
My brother-in-law and my
family lived through that day.

00:15:56.480 --> 00:15:58.630 align:middle line:84%
I thought talking
with him would help.

00:15:58.630 --> 00:16:02.230 align:middle line:10%
>> My wife and I, we would
take turns taking our daughter

00:16:02.230 --> 00:16:05.710 align:middle line:10%
to daycare, and her preschool
is three blocks just north

00:16:05.710 --> 00:16:06.730 align:middle line:10%
of the towers.

00:16:06.730 --> 00:16:09.940 align:middle line:10%
On 9/11, it was my turn to stay
at home and wasn't in a hurry

00:16:09.940 --> 00:16:11.560 align:middle line:10%
to get to work, so
I decided to cook

00:16:11.560 --> 00:16:13.643 align:middle line:10%
a little dinner that
morning, put it in a crockpot

00:16:13.643 --> 00:16:15.300 align:middle line:10%
so we come home and have dinner.

00:16:15.300 --> 00:16:17.560 align:middle line:84%
And as I was doing that,
I was watching the news

00:16:17.560 --> 00:16:20.256 align:middle line:84%
and I saw that the first
tower had been hit.

00:16:20.256 --> 00:16:22.900 align:middle line:84%
>> We have word that a plane
had crashed into one tower.

00:16:22.900 --> 00:16:25.820 align:middle line:10%
>> Watching it on the news
as I was cooking dinner.

00:16:25.820 --> 00:16:27.310 align:middle line:10%
And a horrible thing.

00:16:27.310 --> 00:16:30.620 align:middle line:90%


00:16:30.620 --> 00:16:32.120 align:middle line:90%
I walked outside.

00:16:32.120 --> 00:16:36.190 align:middle line:84%
And as we were standing there,
I was watching, just looking up,

00:16:36.190 --> 00:16:38.202 align:middle line:90%
and I saw the second plane come.

00:16:38.202 --> 00:16:42.330 align:middle line:10%
>> Americans watched in shock as
a second jetliner flew straight

00:16:42.330 --> 00:16:44.020 align:middle line:10%
into the second tower.

00:16:44.020 --> 00:16:49.590 align:middle line:84%
>> The silence was
deafening on my street.

00:16:49.590 --> 00:16:51.800 align:middle line:84%
It was dead quiet and
nobody knew how to act.

00:16:51.800 --> 00:16:55.490 align:middle line:90%


00:16:55.490 --> 00:16:56.980 align:middle line:90%
>> [INAUDIBLE].

00:16:56.980 --> 00:17:00.480 align:middle line:90%
[SIREN SOUNDING]

00:17:00.480 --> 00:17:01.686 align:middle line:90%
[SCREAMING]

00:17:01.686 --> 00:17:06.810 align:middle line:84%
As I was looking up, I noticed
the top of the building tilt,

00:17:06.810 --> 00:17:09.210 align:middle line:84%
and it just tilted a
bit and just came down.

00:17:09.210 --> 00:17:19.790 align:middle line:90%


00:17:19.790 --> 00:17:24.770 align:middle line:84%
I can't-- I can't tell
you how tough that was.

00:17:24.770 --> 00:17:26.690 align:middle line:84%
Now I see this
big waft of smoke,

00:17:26.690 --> 00:17:29.600 align:middle line:84%
and everybody is
turning and running.

00:17:29.600 --> 00:17:31.270 align:middle line:90%
And I started running into it.

00:17:31.270 --> 00:17:34.620 align:middle line:90%


00:17:34.620 --> 00:17:35.420 align:middle line:90%
Excuse me.

00:17:35.420 --> 00:17:38.660 align:middle line:90%
I'm so sorry.

00:17:38.660 --> 00:17:42.020 align:middle line:84%
I started running into it, and
a cop grabbed me by my arm.

00:17:42.020 --> 00:17:46.040 align:middle line:90%


00:17:46.040 --> 00:17:47.265 align:middle line:90%
And he grabbed me by my arm.

00:17:47.265 --> 00:17:48.890 align:middle line:84%
He said, stop, you
can't go down there.

00:17:48.890 --> 00:17:51.000 align:middle line:84%
And I said, my wife and
my daughter are there.

00:17:51.000 --> 00:17:53.760 align:middle line:90%


00:17:53.760 --> 00:17:57.500 align:middle line:90%
And he said, go, just go.

00:17:57.500 --> 00:18:01.485 align:middle line:84%
>> My niece and sister
survived that day.

00:18:01.485 --> 00:18:04.370 align:middle line:84%
But until 9/11,
did we ever think

00:18:04.370 --> 00:18:05.930 align:middle line:84%
how any of these
global incidents

00:18:05.930 --> 00:18:07.745 align:middle line:84%
affect us both
personally and globally?

00:18:07.745 --> 00:18:10.650 align:middle line:90%


00:18:10.650 --> 00:18:15.350 align:middle line:84%
What does the 9/11
memorial serve for us?

00:18:15.350 --> 00:18:19.120 align:middle line:90%
How do we transcend our trauma?

00:18:19.120 --> 00:18:20.290 align:middle line:90%
Where do we go from here?

00:18:20.290 --> 00:18:25.450 align:middle line:90%


00:18:25.450 --> 00:18:27.200 align:middle line:84%
I needed some
inspiration, some hope.

00:18:27.200 --> 00:18:31.080 align:middle line:90%


00:18:31.080 --> 00:18:38.378 align:middle line:84%
>> (SINGING) If I had a hammer,
I'd hammer in the morning,

00:18:38.378 --> 00:18:40.210 align:middle line:90%
I'd hammer in the evening--

00:18:40.210 --> 00:18:42.950 align:middle line:84%
>> As fate would have it, I met
the legendary folk singer Pete

00:18:42.950 --> 00:18:44.435 align:middle line:90%
Seeger at the United Nations.

00:18:44.435 --> 00:18:46.227 align:middle line:84%
[MUSIC - PETE SEEGER, "IF I HAD
 A HAMMER"]

00:18:46.227 --> 00:18:47.880 align:middle line:84%
>> (SINGING) I'd
hammer out danger.

00:18:47.880 --> 00:18:50.250 align:middle line:10%
>> Pete Seeger is one of the
greatest icons of the peace

00:18:50.250 --> 00:18:52.420 align:middle line:10%
and social justice movement.

00:18:52.420 --> 00:18:54.900 align:middle line:10%
He was a true patriot
serving in World War II.

00:18:54.900 --> 00:18:56.400 align:middle line:84%
Never stopped
loving his country,

00:18:56.400 --> 00:18:59.280 align:middle line:84%
even after being blacklisted
during the McCarthy era

00:18:59.280 --> 00:19:01.130 align:middle line:90%
by the US government.

00:19:01.130 --> 00:19:03.838 align:middle line:84%
>> Mr. Seeger, you specifically
declined the protection

00:19:03.838 --> 00:19:05.880 align:middle line:84%
of the Fifth Amendment
and are refusing to answer

00:19:05.880 --> 00:19:06.963 align:middle line:90%
the committee's questions.

00:19:06.963 --> 00:19:07.980 align:middle line:90%
Can you tell us why?

00:19:07.980 --> 00:19:12.480 align:middle line:84%
>> (SINGING) I'd ring
it in the evening.

00:19:12.480 --> 00:19:15.210 align:middle line:84%
>> For 70 years, he was on the
frontlines fighting for justice

00:19:15.210 --> 00:19:16.505 align:middle line:90%
and human rights.

00:19:16.505 --> 00:19:20.465 align:middle line:90%
>> (SINGING) Hey, [INAUDIBLE].

00:19:20.465 --> 00:19:21.950 align:middle line:90%
Ring out love.

00:19:21.950 --> 00:19:25.415 align:middle line:90%
I'd ring out love.

00:19:25.415 --> 00:19:27.395 align:middle line:90%
>> After the UN ceremony--

00:19:27.395 --> 00:19:29.197 align:middle line:90%
[BELL RINGS]

00:19:29.197 --> 00:19:31.530 align:middle line:84%
--Pete invited me to join him
in his hometown of Beacon,

00:19:31.530 --> 00:19:33.930 align:middle line:84%
New York, a bit up the
road from West Point,

00:19:33.930 --> 00:19:36.510 align:middle line:84%
at the heart of the United
States military academy,

00:19:36.510 --> 00:19:39.600 align:middle line:84%
at a place where you can vote
with your car horn for Peace

00:19:39.600 --> 00:19:40.840 align:middle line:90%
or for--

00:19:40.840 --> 00:19:44.750 align:middle line:84%
well, it's not quite war,
but it's certainly not peace.

00:19:44.750 --> 00:19:46.160 align:middle line:10%
How long has this been going on?

00:19:46.160 --> 00:19:49.340 align:middle line:10%
>> About five or six years,
between 12 o'clock and 2

00:19:49.340 --> 00:19:50.870 align:middle line:10%
o'clock.

00:19:50.870 --> 00:19:54.220 align:middle line:84%
Occasionally, I and others have
gone over to shake their hand.

00:19:54.220 --> 00:19:56.630 align:middle line:84%
When I go over,
I always say, I'm

00:19:56.630 --> 00:19:58.640 align:middle line:84%
glad that I live
in a country where

00:19:58.640 --> 00:20:01.850 align:middle line:84%
we can disagree without
trying to shoot each other.

00:20:01.850 --> 00:20:10.778 align:middle line:90%


00:20:10.778 --> 00:20:13.050 align:middle line:90%
>> Seeger is a communist stooge.

00:20:13.050 --> 00:20:13.883 align:middle line:90%
What does that mean?

00:20:13.883 --> 00:20:15.342 align:middle line:84%
>> If you don't
know what it means,

00:20:15.342 --> 00:20:16.760 align:middle line:84%
you better go back
to school then.

00:20:16.760 --> 00:20:18.460 align:middle line:84%
>> You don't want
to talk at all?

00:20:18.460 --> 00:20:21.930 align:middle line:90%
>> We support the troops.

00:20:21.930 --> 00:20:23.590 align:middle line:84%
They're over there
knocking them.

00:20:23.590 --> 00:20:23.950 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:20:23.950 --> 00:20:25.283 align:middle line:90%
Well, these guys are obviously--

00:20:25.283 --> 00:20:27.970 align:middle line:84%
>> Those guys over there, who
think they're going to bring

00:20:27.970 --> 00:20:31.540 align:middle line:84%
peace and prosperity to the
world by blowing bubbles

00:20:31.540 --> 00:20:32.560 align:middle line:90%
and doing dances.

00:20:32.560 --> 00:20:35.910 align:middle line:90%


00:20:35.910 --> 00:20:38.230 align:middle line:84%
Wars have been going
on for 10,000 years.

00:20:38.230 --> 00:20:39.320 align:middle line:90%
This is nothing new.

00:20:39.320 --> 00:20:40.900 align:middle line:84%
>> The guys are
over there to fight.

00:20:40.900 --> 00:20:42.370 align:middle line:90%
We got to support the troops.

00:20:42.370 --> 00:20:43.960 align:middle line:84%
>> And so when you
see those guys,

00:20:43.960 --> 00:20:45.627 align:middle line:84%
you don't think they
support our troops.

00:20:45.627 --> 00:20:47.894 align:middle line:84%
>> I don't care what
they do over there.

00:20:47.894 --> 00:20:51.233 align:middle line:90%
[CAR HORNS HONKING]

00:20:51.233 --> 00:20:54.620 align:middle line:84%
Do people really know
what they're honking for?

00:20:54.620 --> 00:20:56.360 align:middle line:90%
Are they honking for peace?

00:20:56.360 --> 00:20:58.130 align:middle line:90%
Are they honking for war?

00:20:58.130 --> 00:21:02.780 align:middle line:84%
Or are they just as
confused as I am?

00:21:02.780 --> 00:21:10.700 align:middle line:84%
(SINGING) Lordy, don't
leave me all by myself.

00:21:10.700 --> 00:21:12.260 align:middle line:90%
>> God, this is so perplexing.

00:21:12.260 --> 00:21:21.108 align:middle line:84%
(SINGING) Lordy, don't
leave me all by myself.

00:21:21.108 --> 00:21:27.890 align:middle line:84%
Lordy, don't leave
me all by myself.

00:21:27.890 --> 00:21:31.730 align:middle line:84%
>> Why is peace so
difficult to achieve?

00:21:31.730 --> 00:21:35.250 align:middle line:84%
One of my favorite places to go
as a kid was Corona Park, home

00:21:35.250 --> 00:21:40.650 align:middle line:84%
of the 1964 World's Fair
and the symbolic Unisphere.

00:21:40.650 --> 00:21:43.680 align:middle line:84%
Are we numbed by our pop
culture to think that violence

00:21:43.680 --> 00:21:45.670 align:middle line:90%
doesn't traumatize us?

00:21:45.670 --> 00:21:47.910 align:middle line:84%
Are these polarized
forces pulling our world

00:21:47.910 --> 00:21:50.760 align:middle line:90%
backwards or forward?

00:21:50.760 --> 00:21:53.120 align:middle line:84%
>> The greatest exhibit
of its kind ever staged.

00:21:53.120 --> 00:21:56.130 align:middle line:84%
The symbolic Unisphere
was the mecca of millions.

00:21:56.130 --> 00:21:57.900 align:middle line:90%
It was a year of change.

00:21:57.900 --> 00:22:01.710 align:middle line:84%
A year that called upon man to
face new challenges to shape

00:22:01.710 --> 00:22:05.590 align:middle line:90%
the world he dreams about.

00:22:05.590 --> 00:22:07.930 align:middle line:10%
>> Does any of this make sense?

00:22:07.930 --> 00:22:11.650 align:middle line:90%
Comics, video games.

00:22:11.650 --> 00:22:13.330 align:middle line:90%
Is this insane?

00:22:13.330 --> 00:22:17.204 align:middle line:90%
Hiroshima, 9/11.

00:22:17.204 --> 00:22:20.665 align:middle line:90%
The trauma vortex.

00:22:20.665 --> 00:22:22.290 align:middle line:84%
I received the call
from the organizers

00:22:22.290 --> 00:22:23.853 align:middle line:90%
of the Universal Peace Day.

00:22:23.853 --> 00:22:25.770 align:middle line:84%
They've asked me to plant
a tree at the Church

00:22:25.770 --> 00:22:27.390 align:middle line:90%
of St. Paul and St. Andrew.

00:22:27.390 --> 00:22:32.630 align:middle line:90%


00:22:32.630 --> 00:22:34.640 align:middle line:90%
Maybe it's not that hard.

00:22:34.640 --> 00:22:37.820 align:middle line:84%
Maybe peace is as simple as
putting a tree in the ground.

00:22:37.820 --> 00:22:40.100 align:middle line:90%


00:22:40.100 --> 00:22:41.600 align:middle line:84%
I thought it was
an important event,

00:22:41.600 --> 00:22:45.020 align:middle line:84%
so I invited my brother-in-law
and my nephew Gabriel to join.

00:22:45.020 --> 00:22:46.550 align:middle line:90%
>> What is peace?

00:22:46.550 --> 00:22:51.240 align:middle line:90%
>> It's when-- it's when--

00:22:51.240 --> 00:22:56.370 align:middle line:84%
like if there's a lot
of wars or something,

00:22:56.370 --> 00:22:59.600 align:middle line:90%
it's when the wars stop.

00:22:59.600 --> 00:23:03.880 align:middle line:84%
>> I was so excited to return
to my roots of tree planting.

00:23:03.880 --> 00:23:06.730 align:middle line:84%
Turns out, nothing is
as easy as it seems.

00:23:06.730 --> 00:23:10.730 align:middle line:90%


00:23:10.730 --> 00:23:13.870 align:middle line:90%
You know, that's like cement.

00:23:13.870 --> 00:23:15.230 align:middle line:90%
That's not going to grow a root.

00:23:15.230 --> 00:23:17.760 align:middle line:90%


00:23:17.760 --> 00:23:19.550 align:middle line:90%
It's concrete down there.

00:23:19.550 --> 00:23:21.650 align:middle line:84%
Unfortunately, I
don't think this peace

00:23:21.650 --> 00:23:23.877 align:middle line:90%
tree is going to take root yet.

00:23:23.877 --> 00:23:24.791 align:middle line:90%
>> What do we want?

00:23:24.791 --> 00:23:25.705 align:middle line:90%
>> Peace!

00:23:25.705 --> 00:23:26.619 align:middle line:90%
When do we want it?

00:23:26.619 --> 00:23:27.080 align:middle line:90%
>> Now!

00:23:27.080 --> 00:23:29.240 align:middle line:84%
>> Maybe it's time to
take a different approach.

00:23:29.240 --> 00:23:35.090 align:middle line:84%
Maybe joining a larger movement,
a peace movement is the answer.

00:23:35.090 --> 00:23:37.370 align:middle line:84%
The World March for
Peace and Nonviolence

00:23:37.370 --> 00:23:39.270 align:middle line:84%
was celebrating
Gandhi's birthday--

00:23:39.270 --> 00:23:41.910 align:middle line:90%
>> Parrots for peace!

00:23:41.910 --> 00:23:45.200 align:middle line:84%
>> --by reminding us of
Hiroshima and carrying a torch

00:23:45.200 --> 00:23:47.360 align:middle line:90%
around the world.

00:23:47.360 --> 00:23:49.103 align:middle line:90%
Why not join them?

00:23:49.103 --> 00:23:50.395 align:middle line:90%
What inspired you to come down?

00:23:50.395 --> 00:23:53.250 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I'm a longtime
peace activist, 40 years now,

00:23:53.250 --> 00:23:54.050 align:middle line:90%
you know?

00:23:54.050 --> 00:23:55.830 align:middle line:84%
>> And did you serve
in the army at all?

00:23:55.830 --> 00:23:58.020 align:middle line:10%
>> I was in the
army, the infantry.

00:23:58.020 --> 00:24:00.390 align:middle line:84%
I was taught how to
kill when I was 17.

00:24:00.390 --> 00:24:02.730 align:middle line:84%
>> And what taught you
to want to make peace?

00:24:02.730 --> 00:24:05.980 align:middle line:84%
>> I began to seriously consider
this whole business of just

00:24:05.980 --> 00:24:06.780 align:middle line:90%
war.

00:24:06.780 --> 00:24:09.394 align:middle line:84%
There is no such
thing as a just war.

00:24:09.394 --> 00:24:11.262 align:middle line:90%
>> Are we ready to march?

00:24:11.262 --> 00:24:13.597 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah!

00:24:13.597 --> 00:24:14.540 align:middle line:90%
>> We're off.

00:24:14.540 --> 00:24:20.460 align:middle line:84%
Me and about 700 people
and three peace parrots.

00:24:20.460 --> 00:24:23.470 align:middle line:84%
Not the weather we were
expecting, but we're here

00:24:23.470 --> 00:24:24.850 align:middle line:90%
and we're going over the bridge.

00:24:24.850 --> 00:24:28.322 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:24:28.322 --> 00:24:29.314 align:middle line:90%


00:24:29.314 --> 00:24:33.282 align:middle line:10%
(SINGING) Here we go again.

00:24:33.282 --> 00:24:36.754 align:middle line:90%
Here we go again.

00:24:36.754 --> 00:24:39.240 align:middle line:90%
Here we go again.

00:24:39.240 --> 00:24:42.120 align:middle line:84%
>> Is anyone aware about
this world march for peace?

00:24:42.120 --> 00:24:44.390 align:middle line:90%
Does any of this really matter?

00:24:44.390 --> 00:24:50.190 align:middle line:84%
Does one person or protest as
big as this make a difference?

00:24:50.190 --> 00:24:52.050 align:middle line:84%
Is anything in
our world changing

00:24:52.050 --> 00:24:53.340 align:middle line:90%
to a more peaceful way?

00:24:53.340 --> 00:24:56.410 align:middle line:90%


00:24:56.410 --> 00:24:58.920 align:middle line:84%
When we reached the
Manhattan City Hall building,

00:24:58.920 --> 00:25:01.990 align:middle line:84%
I was a bit surprised that
there was no welcome committee.

00:25:01.990 --> 00:25:04.350 align:middle line:84%
We're informed the mayor
was unable to attend

00:25:04.350 --> 00:25:06.040 align:middle line:90%
due to a prior commitment.

00:25:06.040 --> 00:25:09.160 align:middle line:84%
And none of US news bureaus
bothered to cover the event.

00:25:09.160 --> 00:25:12.150 align:middle line:10%
>> If you want to change the
world, start with yourself.

00:25:12.150 --> 00:25:13.440 align:middle line:10%
Be a good example.

00:25:13.440 --> 00:25:16.830 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise, you'll end up being
an angry peace activist, which

00:25:16.830 --> 00:25:18.360 align:middle line:90%
is a contradiction.

00:25:18.360 --> 00:25:21.150 align:middle line:84%
>> Perhaps I'm coming at it
from the wrong direction.

00:25:21.150 --> 00:25:24.078 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps I need to
look with them myself.

00:25:24.078 --> 00:25:27.564 align:middle line:84%
[MUSIC - THE BEACH BOYS,
 "KOKOMO"]

00:25:27.564 --> 00:25:29.075 align:middle line:90%


00:25:29.075 --> 00:25:31.350 align:middle line:84%
Meeting Deepak Chopra
really opened my eyes

00:25:31.350 --> 00:25:33.540 align:middle line:90%
to this idea of inner peace.

00:25:33.540 --> 00:25:36.270 align:middle line:84%
He talked about
meditation, consciousness,

00:25:36.270 --> 00:25:39.680 align:middle line:84%
and his old friend
Maharishi Mahesh Yogi.

00:25:39.680 --> 00:25:41.370 align:middle line:84%
I went online and
read that Maharishi

00:25:41.370 --> 00:25:43.767 align:middle line:84%
had his own university
out in Fairfield, Iowa,

00:25:43.767 --> 00:25:45.600 align:middle line:84%
and that The Beach Boys
were coming to town.

00:25:45.600 --> 00:25:48.470 align:middle line:84%
>> (SINGING) Off
the Florida Keys--

00:25:48.470 --> 00:25:50.955 align:middle line:84%
>> I didn't know who this
Maharishi character was or why

00:25:50.955 --> 00:25:52.920 align:middle line:84%
he would have his
own university.

00:25:52.920 --> 00:25:56.460 align:middle line:84%
I thought, OK, maybe God
is telling me something.

00:25:56.460 --> 00:25:58.250 align:middle line:90%
My girlfriend's from Iowa.

00:25:58.250 --> 00:25:59.905 align:middle line:90%
I could use a break.

00:25:59.905 --> 00:26:02.280 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it would be a good idea
to go away for the weekend.

00:26:02.280 --> 00:26:05.165 align:middle line:84%
So I said, hey Britta, let's
go away and have some fun.

00:26:05.165 --> 00:26:10.015 align:middle line:84%
>> (SINGING) Ooh, I want to
take you to Bermuda, Bahama.

00:26:10.015 --> 00:26:11.955 align:middle line:90%
Come on, pretty mama.

00:26:11.955 --> 00:26:13.895 align:middle line:90%
Key Largo, Montego.

00:26:13.895 --> 00:26:15.850 align:middle line:90%
Baby, why don't we go?

00:26:15.850 --> 00:26:19.120 align:middle line:84%
>> I met Greg a little
over three years ago.

00:26:19.120 --> 00:26:23.322 align:middle line:10%
I was working at a PR firm.

00:26:23.322 --> 00:26:25.780 align:middle line:84%
>> I felt like she was looking
at me like she was giving me

00:26:25.780 --> 00:26:26.470 align:middle line:90%
the blink-blink.

00:26:26.470 --> 00:26:27.845 align:middle line:84%
And I was like,
who is this girl?

00:26:27.845 --> 00:26:30.410 align:middle line:90%
I was like, what are you doing?

00:26:30.410 --> 00:26:32.950 align:middle line:84%
I'm like, I think she
wants to go out with me.

00:26:32.950 --> 00:26:34.750 align:middle line:90%
Maybe that was my arrogant self.

00:26:34.750 --> 00:26:37.810 align:middle line:84%
>> I had called him
strictly about work.

00:26:37.810 --> 00:26:41.560 align:middle line:84%
And out of nowhere, he took
me off guard and he said,

00:26:41.560 --> 00:26:43.697 align:middle line:90%
so are you dating anybody?

00:26:43.697 --> 00:26:45.530 align:middle line:84%
>> I think I sort of
threw her a curve ball.

00:26:45.530 --> 00:26:47.770 align:middle line:84%
And took her like, you
know, about a minute,

00:26:47.770 --> 00:26:48.984 align:middle line:90%
and she's like, yeah, sure.

00:26:48.984 --> 00:26:51.770 align:middle line:90%
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

00:26:51.770 --> 00:26:53.770 align:middle line:84%
Britta and I had a
great time together.

00:26:53.770 --> 00:26:56.650 align:middle line:84%
There was a lot of talk
about this guru Maharishi,

00:26:56.650 --> 00:26:58.300 align:middle line:90%
transcendental meditation.

00:26:58.300 --> 00:27:00.520 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't sure what
it had to do with me.

00:27:00.520 --> 00:27:02.710 align:middle line:84%
After The Beach Boys
concert, I had a chance

00:27:02.710 --> 00:27:04.540 align:middle line:90%
to meet up with Mike Love.

00:27:04.540 --> 00:27:06.960 align:middle line:10%
>> Creativity and more
energy and clarity,

00:27:06.960 --> 00:27:09.700 align:middle line:10%
that that sounds like
something everybody could use.

00:27:09.700 --> 00:27:12.750 align:middle line:84%
It's kind of like you're
on a spiritual safari.

00:27:12.750 --> 00:27:14.870 align:middle line:84%
[MUSIC - MIKE LOVE, "PISCES
 BROTHERS"]

00:27:14.870 --> 00:27:16.680 align:middle line:84%
We'd been on our
"Surfin Safari," we've

00:27:16.680 --> 00:27:19.770 align:middle line:84%
done "Good Vibrations" and
the "Pet Sounds" album and all

00:27:19.770 --> 00:27:22.870 align:middle line:84%
these great songs and had
all these great experiences,

00:27:22.870 --> 00:27:27.450 align:middle line:84%
but this is a whole different
realm that I ventured into.

00:27:27.450 --> 00:27:30.780 align:middle line:84%
>> I was curious at this new
realm and when it all began

00:27:30.780 --> 00:27:33.070 align:middle line:90%
for Mike.

00:27:33.070 --> 00:27:39.220 align:middle line:10%
>> We were invited to go to
Paris, in December of 1967,

00:27:39.220 --> 00:27:43.480 align:middle line:10%
for a Christmas gala that was
going to be televised and sent

00:27:43.480 --> 00:27:44.740 align:middle line:10%
out all over Europe.

00:27:44.740 --> 00:27:47.730 align:middle line:90%


00:27:47.730 --> 00:27:49.330 align:middle line:84%
And during the
rehearsals, we met

00:27:49.330 --> 00:27:51.640 align:middle line:84%
Maharishi, who was
ostensibly going

00:27:51.640 --> 00:27:56.110 align:middle line:84%
to speak on the program
about world peace.

00:27:56.110 --> 00:27:59.325 align:middle line:10%
>> Modern technology says, man
has been using only a small

00:27:59.325 --> 00:28:00.840 align:middle line:10%
portion of the mind.

00:28:00.840 --> 00:28:02.500 align:middle line:84%
Transcendental
meditation is the way

00:28:02.500 --> 00:28:05.580 align:middle line:84%
to enable every man,
to educate every man

00:28:05.580 --> 00:28:09.110 align:middle line:84%
to make use of his
full mental potential.

00:28:09.110 --> 00:28:13.010 align:middle line:84%
Imagine the development in
all fields of civilization

00:28:13.010 --> 00:28:16.840 align:middle line:84%
when every man will be using
his full mental potential.

00:28:16.840 --> 00:28:20.380 align:middle line:84%
>> Maharishi said that if
the forest is to be green,

00:28:20.380 --> 00:28:21.700 align:middle line:90%
every tree must be green.

00:28:21.700 --> 00:28:23.722 align:middle line:90%
(SINGING) Not for fortune.

00:28:23.722 --> 00:28:25.180 align:middle line:84%
If there's going
to peace on Earth,

00:28:25.180 --> 00:28:27.570 align:middle line:84%
everybody has to feel
that quality of peace.

00:28:27.570 --> 00:28:36.126 align:middle line:84%
(SINGING) But for enlightenment
we came to Mahareshi.

00:28:36.126 --> 00:28:38.620 align:middle line:90%
And how sublime.

00:28:38.620 --> 00:28:41.470 align:middle line:84%
>> I always thought of peace
in the '60s as hippies smoking

00:28:41.470 --> 00:28:44.270 align:middle line:90%
marijuana and wearing tie-dyes.

00:28:44.270 --> 00:28:47.870 align:middle line:84%
What does the forest
have to do with peace?

00:28:47.870 --> 00:28:49.970 align:middle line:10%
Mike mentioned a
spiritual retreat in India

00:28:49.970 --> 00:28:53.120 align:middle line:10%
with Maharishi, the Beatles,
and the legendary folk

00:28:53.120 --> 00:28:54.940 align:middle line:10%
singer Donovan.

00:28:54.940 --> 00:28:58.660 align:middle line:10%
Perhaps Donovan can share
some wisdom about this time.

00:28:58.660 --> 00:29:04.210 align:middle line:84%
>> People ask me why and what
led me to India to study with

00:29:04.210 --> 00:29:07.340 align:middle line:90%
the Maharishi Mahesh Yogi.

00:29:07.340 --> 00:29:09.680 align:middle line:84%
>> Far from the noise
and pace of city life,

00:29:09.680 --> 00:29:12.980 align:middle line:84%
in the cool clear air of
Rishikesh, North India,

00:29:12.980 --> 00:29:16.400 align:middle line:84%
we have news reports from the
meditation retreat of Maharishi

00:29:16.400 --> 00:29:20.540 align:middle line:84%
Mahesh Yogi, the man who through
transcendental meditation is

00:29:20.540 --> 00:29:24.770 align:middle line:84%
currently bringing peace
of mind to the Beatles.

00:29:24.770 --> 00:29:27.560 align:middle line:84%
>> When I met The Beatles,
George Harrison and I would

00:29:27.560 --> 00:29:29.730 align:middle line:84%
hang out and we were
looking, looking.

00:29:29.730 --> 00:29:32.950 align:middle line:90%


00:29:32.950 --> 00:29:36.418 align:middle line:84%
What we were searching for
was a super conscious feel.

00:29:36.418 --> 00:29:37.960 align:middle line:84%
[MUSIC - DONOVAN, "HURDY GURDY
 MAN"]

00:29:37.960 --> 00:29:40.823 align:middle line:84%
(SINGING) Thrown like a
star in my vast sleep.

00:29:40.823 --> 00:29:45.870 align:middle line:84%
I opened my eyes to
take a peek to find

00:29:45.870 --> 00:29:52.920 align:middle line:84%
that I was by the sea
gazing with tranquility.

00:29:52.920 --> 00:29:55.260 align:middle line:84%
The human being
lives on three levels

00:29:55.260 --> 00:30:02.130 align:middle line:84%
of consciousness, sleeping,
waking, and dreamless sleep.

00:30:02.130 --> 00:30:08.400 align:middle line:84%
There is a fourth level, which
once contacted, links you

00:30:08.400 --> 00:30:13.140 align:middle line:84%
and unifies you with all
other levels of existence.

00:30:13.140 --> 00:30:16.410 align:middle line:84%
It would produce in
one an understanding

00:30:16.410 --> 00:30:17.820 align:middle line:90%
of the unity of all.

00:30:17.820 --> 00:30:20.740 align:middle line:90%


00:30:20.740 --> 00:30:22.950 align:middle line:84%
And we were looking,
who can teach us?

00:30:22.950 --> 00:30:27.810 align:middle line:84%
And then, one day, Maharishi
appears in our lives.

00:30:27.810 --> 00:30:34.270 align:middle line:84%
>> Just this phenomenon that
we meditate, and we come out,

00:30:34.270 --> 00:30:35.706 align:middle line:90%
and we are more general.

00:30:35.706 --> 00:30:37.248 align:middle line:84%
[MUSIC - DONOVAN, "HURDY GURDY
 MAN"]

00:30:37.248 --> 00:30:42.250 align:middle line:84%
(SINGING) Years of sleep,
time demands a turnaround.

00:30:42.250 --> 00:30:47.252 align:middle line:84%
And once again,
a truth is found.

00:30:47.252 --> 00:30:48.224 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, George.

00:30:48.224 --> 00:30:52.112 align:middle line:90%


00:30:52.112 --> 00:30:57.080 align:middle line:84%
Then when the hurdy gurdy man,
he comes singing the songs.

00:30:57.080 --> 00:31:00.454 align:middle line:90%


00:31:00.454 --> 00:31:08.670 align:middle line:84%
Hurdy gurdy, hurdy gurdy,
hurdy gurdy gurdy, he sang.

00:31:08.670 --> 00:31:13.340 align:middle line:84%
Once you see yourself and the
world from that fourth level,

00:31:13.340 --> 00:31:14.440 align:middle line:90%
everything's different.

00:31:14.440 --> 00:31:17.440 align:middle line:90%


00:31:17.440 --> 00:31:20.960 align:middle line:84%
>> I was truly inspired by Mike
Love, Donovan, and The Beatles,

00:31:20.960 --> 00:31:23.570 align:middle line:90%
but I had a lot of questions.

00:31:23.570 --> 00:31:26.000 align:middle line:84%
What is this fourth
level of consciousness?

00:31:26.000 --> 00:31:27.820 align:middle line:90%
How is everything different?

00:31:27.820 --> 00:31:29.560 align:middle line:84%
Can we really
resolve our conflicts

00:31:29.560 --> 00:31:31.840 align:middle line:90%
by expanding our minds?

00:31:31.840 --> 00:31:34.060 align:middle line:90%
>> We have to start at our mind.

00:31:34.060 --> 00:31:36.820 align:middle line:84%
And in our mind, we
have this crazy idea

00:31:36.820 --> 00:31:38.388 align:middle line:90%
that we can kill each other.

00:31:38.388 --> 00:31:40.180 align:middle line:84%
>> We've all got this
ancient brain in us--

00:31:40.180 --> 00:31:41.590 align:middle line:90%
420 million years old.

00:31:41.590 --> 00:31:44.047 align:middle line:90%
It's a reptile brain.

00:31:44.047 --> 00:31:46.442 align:middle line:90%
[FLUTE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:31:46.442 --> 00:31:49.800 align:middle line:90%


00:31:49.800 --> 00:31:51.140 align:middle line:90%
Reptiles make war.

00:31:51.140 --> 00:31:53.255 align:middle line:90%
It's win-lose with a crocodile.

00:31:53.255 --> 00:31:54.185 align:middle line:90%
[GROWLING]

00:31:54.185 --> 00:31:54.985 align:middle line:90%


00:31:54.985 --> 00:31:57.920 align:middle line:84%
We've got to calm the reptile
in us so that that mammal

00:31:57.920 --> 00:32:01.370 align:middle line:84%
brain, which is half as old, 210
million years old, can emerge.

00:32:01.370 --> 00:32:03.020 align:middle line:84%
Because it's the
mammal brain that

00:32:03.020 --> 00:32:07.130 align:middle line:84%
is about compassion, family,
kinship and getting along.

00:32:07.130 --> 00:32:10.460 align:middle line:10%
>> I went to visit Dan Siegel,
founder of the Mindsight

00:32:10.460 --> 00:32:14.390 align:middle line:10%
Institute, to learn more about
the inner workings of the mind.

00:32:14.390 --> 00:32:17.120 align:middle line:10%
>> And what's really amazing
about this brain is the ancient

00:32:17.120 --> 00:32:21.360 align:middle line:10%
parts evolved, and
the newer parts grew.

00:32:21.360 --> 00:32:24.320 align:middle line:84%
And amazingly, this front
part of the brain right

00:32:24.320 --> 00:32:26.840 align:middle line:84%
behind your forehead
is the very part

00:32:26.840 --> 00:32:31.380 align:middle line:84%
that we use to reflect
on our own inner life.

00:32:31.380 --> 00:32:33.750 align:middle line:84%
It's a natural thing
from our evolution

00:32:33.750 --> 00:32:37.890 align:middle line:84%
that with awareness,
we can actually change

00:32:37.890 --> 00:32:39.580 align:middle line:90%
the pathway of our society.

00:32:39.580 --> 00:32:45.270 align:middle line:90%


00:32:45.270 --> 00:32:49.590 align:middle line:84%
When you do meditative practices
like mindfulness meditation,

00:32:49.590 --> 00:32:53.080 align:middle line:84%
you actually stimulate the
activity of these areas,

00:32:53.080 --> 00:32:54.195 align:middle line:90%
and they begin to grow.

00:32:54.195 --> 00:32:56.252 align:middle line:90%


00:32:56.252 --> 00:32:58.710 align:middle line:84%
The old thought was that when
you're done with adolescence,

00:32:58.710 --> 00:33:00.450 align:middle line:90%
your brain is done growing.

00:33:00.450 --> 00:33:03.240 align:middle line:84%
We now know that's
totally not true.

00:33:03.240 --> 00:33:06.180 align:middle line:84%
It's constantly
responding to input

00:33:06.180 --> 00:33:08.580 align:middle line:90%
that changes its structure.

00:33:08.580 --> 00:33:11.670 align:middle line:84%
These areas would
be getting thicker.

00:33:11.670 --> 00:33:15.270 align:middle line:84%
Everything is stronger
because it's like a muscle,

00:33:15.270 --> 00:33:18.870 align:middle line:84%
that the more you drive energy
and information through them

00:33:18.870 --> 00:33:23.170 align:middle line:84%
by the control, the tension,
you do in meditation.

00:33:23.170 --> 00:33:26.130 align:middle line:84%
The idea of our
human evolution is

00:33:26.130 --> 00:33:28.650 align:middle line:84%
that the area of
the brain where you

00:33:28.650 --> 00:33:32.460 align:middle line:84%
have a meeting of
automatic sensations

00:33:32.460 --> 00:33:35.700 align:middle line:84%
that are coming with reflective,
thoughtful things you've

00:33:35.700 --> 00:33:38.880 align:middle line:84%
learned from the past,
where those two meet

00:33:38.880 --> 00:33:42.780 align:middle line:84%
